25/08/2006
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Leaders of political parties in the new coalition government signed a pledge Thursday (24 August) to revive the country's economy. 
Officials from the VMRO-DPMNE and seven other parties pledged to work for better living standards over the next four years. 
Among the key goals are reducing poverty levels, creating an investment friendly business climate and improving the infrastructure. 
(MIA, Makfax, A1 TV - 24/08/06)
